        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/jzhou/{size}/445_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-02-07T05:27:15.945Z",
        "cooked": "<p>If an ACTOR has no wait() statement, then it should be declared as a normal function, which executes without blocking. ACTOR should be used to encapsulate async functions.</p>\n<p>Specifically, the ACTOR compiler will translate an actor into 2 C++ classes and a function, with automatically generated callbacks and their invocations when a future is ready.</p>",
