      {
        "id": 10661,
        "name": "Markus Pilman",
        "username": "markus.pilman",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/{size}/379_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-02-07T16:35:03.940Z",
        "cooked": "<p>As <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/jzhou\">@jzhou</a> pointed out, you should not use <code>ACTOR</code> for functions without any <code>wait</code> statements as there is some overhead.</p>\n<p>In addition to the 2 generated classes, calling an actor will create an object on the heap. It\u2019s also a bit weird: when returning from an <code>ACTOR Future&lt;T&gt; ...</code> function, you must return something of type <code>T</code> and not <code>Future&lt;T&gt;</code>.</p>\n<p>Reading the generated code shouldn\u2019t be too hard and I would recommend you do that. For example:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">ACTOR Future&lt;Void&gt; foo() {\n\treturn Void();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>This actor with no wait statement will result in this code</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">// This generated class is to be used only via foo()\nclass FooActor final : public Actor&lt;Void&gt;, public FastAllocated&lt;FooActor&gt;, public FooActorState&lt;FooActor&gt; {\npublic:\n\tusing FastAllocated&lt;FooActor&gt;::operator new;\n\tusing FastAllocated&lt;FooActor&gt;::operator delete;\n#pragma clang diagnostic push\n#pragma clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wdelete-non-virtual-dtor\"\n\tvoid destroy() override { ((Actor&lt;Void&gt;*)this)-&gt;~Actor(); operator delete(this); }\n#pragma clang diagnostic pop\n\tFooActor() \n\t\t : Actor&lt;Void&gt;(),\n\t\t   FooActorState&lt;FooActor&gt;()\n\t{\n\t\t#ifdef ENABLE_SAMPLING\n\t\tthis-&gt;lineage.setActorName(\"foo\");\n\t\tLineageScope _(&amp;this-&gt;lineage);\n\t\t#endif\n\t\tthis-&gt;a_body1();\n\n\t}\n\tvoid cancel() override\n\t{\n\t\tauto wait_state = this-&gt;actor_wait_state;\n\t\tthis-&gt;actor_wait_state = -1;\n\t\tswitch (wait_state) {\n\t\t}\n\n\t}\n};\n}\n[[nodiscard]] Future&lt;Void&gt; foo(  ) {\n\treturn Future&lt;Void&gt;(new FooActor());\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>As you can see, there\u2019s quite some overhead. An equivalent function would be:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">Future&lt;Void&gt; foo() {\n\treturn Void();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Which will be much cheaper.</p>",
